Add original_content-aware updates

Two new functions UpdateFunc and UpdateBytesFunc added.
They introduce ability to make updates based on previous/original data (instead of simple override).
Simple use case is to increment some field atomically.

UpdateFunc is using map[string]interface{} - as other db.* functions.

Merge pull request #73 from dchapes/patch-1

Correct Map for file sizes larger than 1<<31 - 1

Correct Map for file sizes larger than 1<<31 - 1

int(int64value) doesn't always return <0 when an int is 32 bits.
Long ago, Go moved to 64 bit int's on amd64 and mmap-ing large files works fine.
Should not panic when an error return is the sane thing to do.
Remove un-used ANON (which should probably have been set to syscall.MAP_ANON anyway).
